From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 6 Oct 2025 22:56:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: fix wrong totalram usage on
 damos_get_node_memcg_used_bp()

The totalram value is in pages, but the code assumes it is in bytes.  As
a result, the goal score calculation is significantly wrong.  Fix the
wrong usage of the metric.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index b627d21c29a6..9a7538fdb33e 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -2053,7 +2053,7 @@ static unsigned long damos_get_node_memcg_used_bp(
 	rcu_read_unlock();
 
 	si_meminfo_node(&i, goal->nid);
-	return used_pages * PAGE_SIZE * 10000 / i.totalram;
+	return used_pages * 10000 / i.totalram;
 }
 #else
 static __kernel_ulong_t damos_get_node_mem_bp(
-- 
2.39.5

